class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    // 
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();

    // 
    public List<List<Integer>> subsets(int[] nums) {
        backtrack(nums, 0);
        return res;
    }

    // 
    void backtrack(int[] nums, int start) {

        // 
        res.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
        
        // 
        for (int i = start; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // 
            track.addLast(nums[i]);
            //  start 
            backtrack(nums, i + 1);
            // 
            track.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

func subsets(nums []int) [][]int {
    var res [][]int
    // 
    var track []int
    
    // 
    var backtrack func(int)
    backtrack = func(start int) {
        // 
        res = append(res, append([]int(nil), track...))
        
        // 
        for i := start; i < len(nums); i++ {
            // 
            track = append(track, nums[i])
            //  start 
            backtrack(i + 1)
            // 
            track = track[:len(track)-1]
        }
    }

    backtrack(0)
    return res
}

java 
class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    // 
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();

    // 
    public List<List<Integer>> combine(int n, int k) {
        backtrack(1, n, k);
        return res;
    }

    void backtrack(int start, int n, int k) {
        // base case
        if (k == track.size()) {
            //  k 
            res.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
            return;
        }
        
        // 
        for (int i = start; i <= n; i++) {
            // 
            track.addLast(i);
            //  start 
            backtrack(i + 1, n, k);
            // 
            track.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

func combine(n int, k int) [][]int {

        // base case

            //  k 
            res = append(res, append([]int(nil), track...))
            return

class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    // 
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();
    // track  true
    boolean[] used;

    // 
    public List<List<Integer>> permute(int[] nums) {
        used = new boolean[nums.length];
        backtrack(nums);
        return res;
    }

    // 
    void backtrack(int[] nums) {
        // base case
        if (track.size() == nums.length) {
            // 
            res.add(new LinkedList(track));
            return;
        }

        // 
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            //  track 
            if (used[i]) {
                continue;
            }
            // 
            used[i] = true;
            track.addLast(nums[i]);
            // 
            backtrack(nums);
            // 
            track.removeLast();
            used[i] = false;
        }
    }
}

python 
class Solution:
    def __init__(self):
        # 
        self.res = []
        # 
        self.track = []
        # track  true
        self.used = []
    
    # 
    def permute(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
        self.used = [False] * len(nums)
        self.backtrack(nums)
        return self.res
    
    # 
    def backtrack(self, nums: List[int]) -> None:
        # base case
        if len(self.track) == len(nums):
            # 
            self.res.append(self.track[:])
            return
        
        # 
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            #  track 
            if self.used[i]:
                continue
            # 
            self.used[i] = True
            self.track.append(nums[i])
            # 
            self.backtrack(nums)
            # 
            self.track.pop()
            self.used[i] = False
go 
func permute(nums []int) [][]int {
    var res [][]int
    // 
    var track []int
    // track  true
    used := make([]bool, len(nums))

    backtrack(nums, &res, track, used)

    return res
}

// 
func backtrack(nums []int, res *[][]int, track []int, used []bool) {
    // base case
    if len(track) == len(nums) {
        // 
        tmp := make([]int, len(track))
        copy(tmp, track)
        *res = append(*res, tmp)
        return
    }

    // 
    for i := 0; i < len(nums); i++ {
        //  track 
        if used[i] {
            continue
        }
        // 
        used[i] = true
        track = append(track, nums[i])
        // 
        backtrack(nums, res, track, used)
        // 
        track = track[:len(track)-1]
        used[i] = false
    }
}

    // base case
    if (track.length === nums.length) {
        // 
        res.push([...track]);
        return;

    //

        //  track 
        if (used[i]) {
            continue;
        }
        // 
        used[i] = true;
        track.push(nums[i]);
        // 
        backtrack(nums, res, track, used);
        // 
        track.pop();
        used[i] = false;
    }

class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();

    public List<List<Integer>> subsetsWithDup(int[] nums) {
        // 
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        backtrack(nums, 0);
        return res;
    }

    void backtrack(int[] nums, int start) {
        // 
        res.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
        
        for (int i = start; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // 
            if (i > start && nums[i] == nums[i - 1]) {
                continue;
            }
            track.addLast(nums[i]);
            backtrack(nums, i + 1);
            track.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

func subsetsWithDup(nums []int) [][]int {
    var res [][]int
    var track []int
    
    // 
    sort.Ints(nums)
    backtrack(nums, &track, &res, 0)

func backtrack(nums []int, track *[]int, res *[][]int, start int) {
    // 
    tmp := make([]int, len(*track))
    copy(tmp, *track)
    *res = append(*res, tmp)
    
    for i := start; i < len(nums); i++ {
        // 
        if i > start && nums[i] == nums[i-1] {
            continue
        }
        *track = append(*track, nums[i])
        backtrack(nums, track, res, i+1)
        *track = (*track)[:len(*track)-1]
    }
}

java 
class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    // 
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();
    //  track 
    int trackSum = 0;

    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum2(int[] candidates, int target) {
        if (candidates.length == 0) {
            return res;
        }
        // 
        Arrays.sort(candidates);
        backtrack(candidates, 0, target);
        return res;
    }

    // 
    void backtrack(int[] nums, int start, int target) {
        // base case
        if (trackSum == target) {
            res.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
            return;
        }
        // base case
        if (trackSum > target) {
            return;
        }

        // 
        for (int i = start; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // 
            if (i > start && nums[i] == nums[i - 1]) {
                continue;
            }
            // 
            track.add(nums[i]);
            trackSum += nums[i];
            // 
            backtrack(nums, i + 1, target);
            // 
            track.removeLast();
            trackSum -= nums[i];
        }
    }
}

class Solution:
    def __init__(self):
        self.res = []
        # 
        self.track = []
        #  track 
        self.trackSum = 0
    
    def combinationSum2(self, candidates: List[int], target: int) -> List[List[int]]:
        if not candidates:
            return self.res
        # 
        candidates.sort()
        self.backtrack(candidates, 0, target)
        return self.res
    
    # 
    def backtrack(self, nums: List[int], start: int, target: int):
        # base case
        if self.trackSum == target:
            self.res.append(self.track[:])
            return
        # base case
        if self.trackSum > target:
            return
        
        # 
        for i in range(start, len(nums)):
            # 
            if i > start and nums[i] == nums[i - 1]:
                continue
            # 
            self.track.append(nums[i])
            self.trackSum += nums[i]
            # 
            self.backtrack(nums, i + 1, target)
            # 
            self.track.pop()
            self.trackSum -= nums[i]
go 
func combinationSum2(candidates []int, target int) [][]int {
    var res [][]int
    var track []int
    //  track 
    var trackSum int

    // 
    sort.Ints(candidates)
    backtrack(candidates, target, 0, &track, &res, &trackSum)

    return res
}

// 
func backtrack(nums []int, target, start int, track *[]int, res *[][]int, trackSum *int) {
    // base case
    if *trackSum == target {
        tmp := make([]int, len(*track))
        copy(tmp, *track)
        *res = append(*res, tmp)
        return
    }
    // base case
    if *trackSum > target {
        return
    }

    // 
    for i := start; i < len(nums); i++ {
        // 
        if i > start && nums[i] == nums[i-1] {
            continue
        }
        // 
        *track = append(*track, nums[i])
        *trackSum += nums[i]
        // 
        backtrack(nums, target, i+1, track, res, trackSum)
        // 
        *track = (*track)[:len(*track)-1]
        *trackSum -= nums[i]
    }
}

    let trackSum = 0;

    // 
    candidates.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    
    var backtrack = function(nums, target, start) {
        // base case
        if (trackSum === target) {
            res.push([...track]);
            return;
        }
        // base case
        if (trackSum > target) {
            return;
        }

        // 
        for (let i = start; i < nums.length; i++) {
            // 
            if (i > start && nums[i] === nums[i - 1]) {
                continue;
            }
            // 
            track.push(nums[i]);
            trackSum += nums[i];
            // 
            backtrack(nums, target, i + 1);
            // 
            track.pop();
            trackSum -= nums[i];
        }
    };

    backtrack(candidates, target, 0);

    return res;
};

class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();
    boolean[] used;

    public List<List<Integer>> permuteUnique(int[] nums) {
        // 
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        used = new boolean[nums.length];
        backtrack(nums);
        return res;
    }

    void backtrack(int[] nums) {
        if (track.size() == nums.length) {
            res.add(new LinkedList(track));
            return;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (used[i]) {
                continue;
            }
            // 
            if (i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i - 1] && !used[i - 1]) {
                continue;
            }
            track.add(nums[i]);
            used[i] = true;
            backtrack(nums);
            track.removeLast();
            used[i] = false;
        }
    }
}

python 
class Solution:
    def __init__(self):
        self.res = []
        self.track = []
        self.used = []
    
    def permuteUnique(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[List[int]]:
        # 
        nums.sort()
        self.used = [False] * len(nums)
        self.backtrack(nums)
        return self.res
    
    def backtrack(self, nums: List[int]) -> None:
        if len(self.track) == len(nums):
            self.res.append(self.track[:])
            return

        for i in range(len(nums)):
            if self.used[i]:
                continue
            # 
            if i > 0 and nums[i] == nums[i - 1] and not self.used[i - 1]:
                continue
            self.track.append(nums[i])
            self.used[i] = True
            self.backtrack(nums)
            self.track.pop()
            self.used[i] = False
go 
func permuteUnique(nums []int) [][]int {
    var res [][]int
    var track []int
    used := make([]bool, len(nums))

    // 
    sort.Ints(nums)
    backtrack(nums, &res, track, used)
    return res
}

func backtrack(nums []int, res *[][]int, track []int, used []bool) {
    if len(track) == len(nums) {
        tmp := make([]int, len(track))
        copy(tmp, track)
        *res = append(*res, tmp)
        return
    }

    for i := 0; i < len(nums); i++ {
        if used[i] {
            continue
        }
        // 
        if i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i-1] && !used[i-1] {
            continue
        }
        track = append(track, nums[i])
        used[i] = true
        backtrack(nums, res, track, used)
        track = track[:len(track)-1]
        used[i] = false
    }
}

        res.push(track.slice());
        return;

        if (used[i]) {
            continue;

        if (i > 0 && nums[i] === nums[i - 1] && !used[i - 1]) {
            continue;
        }
        track.push(nums[i]);
        used[i] = true;
        backtrack(nums, used, track, res);
        track.pop();
        used[i] = false;
    }

void backtrack(int[] nums, LinkedList<Integer> track) {
    if (track.size() == nums.length) {
        res.add(new LinkedList(track));
        return;
    }

    // 
    //  -10 <= nums[i] <= 10
    int prevNum = -666;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
        // 
        if (used[i]) {
            continue;

        if (nums[i] == prevNum) {
            continue;
        }

        track.add(nums[i]);
        used[i] = true;
        //

        backtrack(nums, track);

        track.removeLast();

    }

class Solution {

    List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();
    // 
    LinkedList<Integer> track = new LinkedList<>();
    //  track 
    int trackSum = 0;

    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum(int[] candidates, int target) {
        if (candidates.length == 0) {
            return res;
        }
        backtrack(candidates, 0, target);
        return res;
    }

    // 
    void backtrack(int[] nums, int start, int target) {
        // base case
        if (trackSum == target) {
            res.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
            return;
        }
        // base case
        if (trackSum > target) {
            return;
        }
        // 
        for (int i = start; i < nums.length; i++) {
            //  nums[i]
            trackSum += nums[i];
            track.add(nums[i]);
            // 
            backtrack(nums, i, target);
            // 
            //  nums[i]
            trackSum -= nums[i];
            track.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

    backtrack = func(nums []int, start int) {
        // base case
        if trackSum == target {

        if trackSum > target {

            backtrack(nums, i)
            //  nums[i]
            trackSum -= nums[i]
            track = track[:len(track)-1]
        }
    }

for (int i = 0, last = -1; i < nums.length; ++i) {
    if (last > -1 && nums[i] == nums[last]) continue;
    if (visited[i])   continue;
    // make choice
    last = i;
    visited[i] = true;
    path.add(nums[i]);
    
    // recursive call
    recur(path, nums);
    
    // cancel choice
    visited[i] = false;
    path.removeLast();
}

leetcode 39 

class Solution:
    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self.res = []
        self.tarck = []
        self.total = 0

    def find_all(self, nums: List[int], start: int, target: int):
        if self.total == target:
            self.res.append(self.tarck[:])
            return

        if self.total > target:
            return

        for i in range(start, len(nums)):
            # 2,3,33,2,3
            if len(self.tarck) > 0 and nums[i] < self.tarck[-1]:
                continue

            self.tarck.append(nums[i])
            self.total += nums[i]
            self.find_all(nums, start, target)
            self.tarck.pop()
            self.total -= nums[i]

    def combinationSum(self, candidates: List[int], target: int) -> List[List[int]]:
        self.find_all(sorted(candidates), 0, target)
        return self.res

class Solution {
    var track = [Int]()
    var res = [[Int]]()
    func subsetsWithDup(_ nums: [Int]) -> [[Int]] {
        let sorted = nums.sorted()
        backtrack(sorted, 0)
        return res
    }
    func backtrack(_ nums: [Int], _ start: Int) {
        res.append(track)
        for i in start..<nums.count {
            if i > start && nums[i] == nums[i - 1] {
                continue
            }
            track.append(nums[i])
            backtrack(nums, start+1)
            track.removeLast()
        }
    }
}

class Solution {
    List<List<Integer>> result=new LinkedList<>();
    public List<List<Integer>> permuteUnique(int[] nums) {
        process(nums,new LinkedList<>(),new boolean[nums.length]);
        return result;
    }

    public void process(int[] nums, LinkedList<Integer> track,boolean[] used){
        if(track.size()==nums.length){
            result.add(new LinkedList<>(track));
            return;
        }

        HashSet<Integer> set=new HashSet<>();

        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(used[i]) continue;
            if(set.contains(nums[i])) continue;
            track.add(nums[i]);
            used[i]=true;
            set.add(nums[i]);
            process(nums,track,used);
            used[i]=false;
            track.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

class Solution {

    private List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();

    private LinkedList<Integer> trace = new LinkedList<>();

    private boolean[] used;

    private int sum;

    private int target;

    /**
         target backtrace
     */
    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum(int[] candidates, int target) {
        Arrays.sort(candidates);
        this.target = target;
        LinkedList<Integer> newCandidatesList = new LinkedList<>();
        for (int i:candidates) {
            int temp = target / i;
            for (int j=0;j<temp;j++) {
                newCandidatesList.add(i);
            }
        }
        int[] newCandidates = new int[newCandidatesList.size()];
        int j=0;
        for (int i:newCandidatesList) {
            newCandidates[j++] = i;
        }
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(newCandidates));
        backtrace(newCandidates, 0);
        return res;
    }

    private void backtrace(int[] candidates, int start) {
        if (sum==target) {
            res.add(new LinkedList(trace));
            //  0 
            return;
        }

        for (int i=start;i<candidates.length;i++) {
            int curSum = sum + candidates[i];
            if (curSum>target) {
                return;
            }

            // 
            if (i>start && candidates[i]==candidates[i-1]) {
                continue;
            }

            // 
            sum = curSum;
            trace.add(candidates[i]);

            //  i+1,  start+1
            backtrace(candidates, i+1);

            sum -= candidates[i];
            trace.removeLast();
        }
    }
}

class Solution {

    private List<List<Integer>> res = new LinkedList<>();

    private LinkedList<Integer> trace = new LinkedList<>();

    private Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

    private int size;

    // 
    public List<List<Integer>> permuteUnique(int[] nums) {
        size = nums.length;
        for (int i:nums) {
            map.put(i, 1+map.getOrDefault(i, 0));
        }
        backtrace();
        return res;
    }

    private void backtrace() {
        if (trace.size()==size) {
            res.add(new LinkedList(trace));
            return;
        }

        // 
        for (int key:map.keySet()) {
            int value = map.get(key);
            if (value==0) {
                continue;
            }

            trace.add(key);
            map.put(key, value-1);

            backtrace();

            trace.removeLast();
            map.put(key, value);
        }
    }
}

import (
    "sort"
)

func combinationSum2(candidates []int, target int) [][]int {
    track :=[]int{}
    res := [][]int{}
    var sum int
    sort.Ints(candidates)
    var backtrack func(int)
    backtrack =func(start int){
        if sum == target {
            temp:=make([]int,len(track))
            copy(temp,track)
            res=append(res,temp)
            return
        }
        if (sum>target){
            return
        }
        for i:=start;i<len(candidates);i++{
            if i>start && candidates[i]==candidates[i-1]{
                continue
            }

            track=append(track,candidates[i])
            sum+=candidates[i]
            backtrack(i+1)
            track=track[:len(track)-1]
            sum-=candidates[i]
        }
    }
    backtrack(0)
    return res
}
